Description: The transmission network includes four types of substation depending on their transformation capacity and their technology level (current, modern).;Definition of the voltage levels (according to Hydro-Quebec): ; - High voltage level above 35 kV (large scale industry); - Medium voltage level nominal voltage between phases is 750 V- 34.5 kV (medium to small scale industry, service sector; - Low voltage level below 750 V (Households)
